  "prompt": "Are Territorial army officers getting permanent commission now a days?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, the Indian Territorial Army (TA) primarily provides part-time military service to its officers and personnel. Traditionally, TA officers have not been granted permanent commissions; they typically serve for a limited period, which can extend beyond the initial commitment based on performance and needs.\n\nHowever, there have been discussions and considerations regarding the full-time absorption of some TA personnel into regular army positions or offering pathways for career advancement, but significant policy changes can take time to implement.\n\nFor the latest and most accurate information, including any recent developments on the status of Territorial Army officers and permanent commissions, I recommend checking the official websites of the Indian Army or relevant government notifications, or news sources covering military matters in India.",
